    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-29T21:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-29T21:13:00-05:00" n="603"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6271: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macgowan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-30T11:00:00+08:47">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1920—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. The following resolution was adopted unanimously yesterday: “Observing
                    principle non-interference Russian internal affairs, diplomatic representatives
                    of Allies recommend in case of disorders that the Allied military commanders
                    limit their action to securing the lives and property of peaceful residents”.
                    Repeated Tokyo [and] Consul General Stephen [<hi rend="italic">Harris?</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Macgowan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
